1
00:00:04,630 --> 00:00:06,775
So many things are possible,

2
00:00:07,161 --> 00:00:08,495
we have to be open.

3
00:00:08,495 --> 00:00:12,329
Guru Mahārāj says,
“Cast your faith towards the Infinite, towards Kṛṣṇa”,

4
00:00:12,329 --> 00:00:14,570
whatever little faith we have.

5
00:00:14,816 --> 00:00:17,495
[Salvadore Dali, Do You Believe in God?]

6
00:00:17,495 --> 00:00:25,271
I mentioned Dali, Salvadore Dali, 
the surrealist painter.

7
00:00:25,271 --> 00:00:29,746
When they said to him,
“Dali, do you believe in God?”

8
00:00:29,746 --> 00:00:35,410
and he said,
“Yes, but I have no faith”,

9
00:00:35,410 --> 00:00:38,836
that was, I thought, oh,
honest answer!

10
00:00:38,836 --> 00:00:40,253
He’s saying “Yes!”

11
00:00:40,253 --> 00:00:44,304
And I believe that everyone 
believes in God, actually.

12
00:00:44,304 --> 00:00:46,877
This was my own opinion:

13
00:00:46,877 --> 00:00:49,079
everyone does.

14
00:00:49,079 --> 00:00:54,328
But, as Avadhūt Mahārāj will say,
“They need association.”

15
00:00:54,328 --> 00:00:59,054
Whenever someone … he goes,
“Oh, they need association”,

16
00:00:59,054 --> 00:01:00,912
and he’s right.

17
00:01:00,912 --> 00:01:04,113
Sthāne sthitāḥ śruti–gatāḿ tanu–vāń–manobhir
(SB: 10.14.3),

18
00:01:04,113 --> 00:01:05,995
when you get this association,

19
00:01:05,995 --> 00:01:08,606
bhaktyā sañjātayā bhaktyā (SB: 11.3.31),

20
00:01:08,606 --> 00:01:10,870
[it] ignites the candle, the flame,

21
00:01:10,870 --> 00:01:13,744
of Krishna conception in the heart.

22
00:01:13,744 --> 00:01:18,949
These are metaphors:
‘flame’, ‘candle’, ‘seed’.

23
00:01:19,933 --> 00:01:26,125
It's always awakened, ignited,
planted, grown, developed,

24
00:01:26,125 --> 00:01:30,376
by association with a proper agent,
a real agent.

25
00:01:30,376 --> 00:01:33,495
That’s the concept.

